topnews: President Obama landed in Cuba for his historic trip to the island nation, which will include diplomatic meetings with high-level officials. But for the White House, it's the chance to talk directly with everyday Cubans that matters most

Another Donald Trump rally was plagued by violence when a protester was punched in the face and kicked while being escorted out the Republican front-runners event in Arizona. The candidate has denied that there's been any violence at his events

Turkey's interior minister identified the suicide bomber who killed four foreign tourists in Istanbul as a militant with links to the Islamic State of Iraq and Greater Syria. Minister Efkan Ala said the bomber was Turkish citizen Mehmet Ozturk

Indian Wells Tennis Garden CEO Raymond Moore told reporters that he thinks male players have carried the sport of tennis. They ride on coattails of the men. They dont make any decisions and they are lucky," he said

Terror suspect Salah Abdeslam has told investigators he was planning to "restart something" from Brussels. Authorities are taking the claim seriously because they've found heavy weapons and a new network of people around him in Belgium

Thirteen people died and 30 others were injured Sunday after a bus carrying foreign exchange university students crashed in Spain. The bus was carrying more than 50 passengers when it appeared to have hit barriers on the right-hand side of the highway

series. The animated Disney film took in $38 million to take first place and pass the $200 million mark domestically
Paint company Sherwin-Williams is buying rival Valspar for $11.3 billion in a move that it says will expand its reach in Asia and Europe. Sherwin-Williams will pay $113 per share in cash

A Chinese journalist who disappeared last week was in fact detained by law-enforcement authorities as he attempted to travel to Hong Kong from Beijing, his lawyer says. Jia Jia's arrest is the latest in an ongoing crackdown on lawyers, journalists and activists

Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell tried to shut down Beltway musings that President Obama's latest pick for the Supreme Court could still find a way to be confirmed in the lame duck session if Hillary Clinton wins the election

Flight recorders from the Flydubai passenger jet that crashed in southern Russia, killing all 62 people on board, are significantly damaged, authorities said, but fficials were working to recover the information from the damaged recorders
Actor and director Tyler Perry spoke to TIME ahead of his live musical special
, which follows the last days of Jesus' life on earth. He also talked about the controversy over the Oscars, and whether he'll endorse a presidential candidate
